<TITLE> CU reopens after a week </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 23 (bdnews24.com) Chittagong University reopened on Saturday after the campus was closed for one week following clashes between Bangladesh Chhatra League and Islami Chhatra Shibir. Additional police were deployed on the campus to prevent a recurrence. Classes were held in a few departments, but the students attended in poor numbers. Authorities closed the university for a week after 25 students were injured on May 15 as the pro-Awami League BCL and Jamaat-e-Islami- backed ICS activists clashed to take control of the residential halls. The police later arrested 16 students raiding halls and cottages on the campus. Authorities also slapped ban on all political activities and rallies. Vice-chancellor Dr Abu Yusuf told bdnews24.com that the situation on the campus was normal. The presence of students was also satisfactory on the first day, he said. The police and authorities have been instructed to keep the situation normal, the VC said. bdnew
